<p style="margin: 0px;">Many of our associates are parents who have to find quality child care in order to work. Others are now, or soon will be, helping their parents or other relatives face the challenges associated with growing older.
</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 0px;">
Our Dependent Care programs help associates by providing referrals to quality care facilities - both for children and adult dependents. They assist associates in obtaining care they can be comfortable with, while increasing the overall availability of quality, licensed dependent care in our communities.
</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 0px;">
We offer several dependent care programs to help associates locate and pay for quality dependent care:
</p>
<ul>
	<li><span class="bd">Child Care Plus.</span> Depending on the associate's eligibility and the child's age, Bank of America will reimburse up to $175 per month per child</li>
	<li><span class="bd">Dependent care reimbursement account.</span> Allows you to use pre-tax deductions to pay for dependent care expenses, which lowers your taxable income</li>
	<li><span class="bd">Other dependent care programs.</span> Bank of America funds other dependent care programs throughout our communities. Projects include:
		<ul type="circle">
			<li>Inclement weather programs and summer camp</li>
			<li>Near-site childcare centers in locations such as Charlotte, Jacksonville and St. Louis</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
<H2 class="p" style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px; padding: 0px;"><span class="bd">Child Care Plus</span></H2>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;">Child Care Plus helps associates pay for child care expenses by reimbursing a portion of the costs for each child in care. Company contribution is determined by age of child and type of care (licensed or informal).
</p>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px;">
Depending on the associate's eligibility and the child's age, Bank of America will reimburse up to $175 per month per child.
</p>
